  "text": "Before we write code, let's understand the building blocks. A VPC, or Virtual Private Cloud, is your isolated network in Azure BU. Think of it as your own private data center in the cloud, completely separate from other customers. Subnets divide your VPC into smaller networks, and you typically place one subnet per availability zone for high availability zone for high availability zone. Root tables act as traffic directors, telling packets where to go, whether to stay within the VPC, reach another subnet, or add a stagglature to an N-cathedral or group.",
